article.headline: IUPUI 79, Centenary 69
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- George Hill scored 15 points before fouling out with 2:30 left to lead IUPUI to a 63-52 victory over Centenary on Thursday night in a Mid-Continent Conference game. Hill went 9-of-11 from the free-throw line. Brandon Cole and Matt Burks each had 12 points as the Jaguars (10-7, 5-1 Mid-Con) leaped out to their best-ever start in the conference. The Gents (3-14, 1-5) outshot IUPUI from the field 41.7 percent to 36.3 percent. But the Jaguars went 21-of-29 from the line, compared with Centenary's 5-of-11. Brian Baumann led Centenary with 17 points, including 4-of-5 3-pointers. Chris Watson, with 12, was the only other Gent in double figures. The Jaguars led 28-21 at the break, but Centenary tied it up three times before IUPUI took the lead for good. The Gents tied the game at 44 on a Larry Logan jumper with 9:20 left, but IUPUI went on a 19-8 run for the win.
